         <abstract id="aspace_9be16e8c0d2bcb47d9d351766cf7c1dd">Eleven letters between Ramon Llado, a Republican soldier in the Spanish Civil War, and his family. Seven letters are from Ramon to his wife, Concepcion. Three letters are from Concepcion to Ramon, and one letter is to Ramon from his sister, Dionisia, and his brother-in-law.</abstract>
      </did>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_cc89f52c98a4ebc7858c8b302096b48c">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Eleven letters between Ramon Llado, a Republican soldier in the Spanish Civil War, and his family. Seven letters are from Ramon to his wife, Concepcion. Three letters are from Concepcion to Ramon, and one letter is to Ramon from his sister, Dionisia, and his brother-in-law.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_654b82b61b209218213a11e682ff1950">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Transferred by the Librarian for the Latin American and Iberian Collections. Purchased by the Librarian for the Latin American and Iberian Collections from Kevin Jackson, 2017.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_425fda7d118a458222fe8088c7ae5462">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Ramon Llado served in the Spanish Civil War as a Republican soldier in a machine gun company, 227th Mixed Brigade, 42nd Division, 905 Batallion Company Ametralladora.</p>  
      </bioghist>
